      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "On systems with a single GPU, this method returns the default device object; see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metal/1433401-mtlcreatesystemdefaultdevice"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". On systems with more than one GPU, this method returns the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metal/mtldevice"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " that was last used to composite and present the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/cametallayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". This device object usually corresponds to the GPU associated with the screen that’s displaying the layer. If you set the layer’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/cametallayer/1478163-device"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to this device object, you reduce the number of cross-GPU texture copies that Core Animation must perform to present the layer’s contents onscreen."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
